6. INTERFACE STANDARDS

6.1 Hardware Interfaces

· Quantum Bus: Q-Connect 2.0 (coaxial or fiber, 20GHz bandwidth)
· Neuromorphic Mesh: NeuroFabric (serial differential, 40Gbps per lane)
· Edge Node: QUENNE-Edge (PoE++, 4x 10GbE, PCIe 5.0)
· Power: 48VDC with intelligent power sharing

6.2 Software APIs

```python
# Example Core API
class QUENNECore:
    def perceive(self, sensors: Dict) -> QuantumState:
        """Convert sensor data to quantum state representation"""
        
    def reason(self, state: QuantumState, context: Context) -> Inference:
        """Perform state-aware inference"""
        
    def act(self, decision: Decision) -> Action:
        """Execute decision through actuators"""
        
    def learn(self, experience: Experience) -> None:
        """Update cognitive models based on outcomes"""
        
    def regulate(self) -> HomeostaticStatus:
        """Adjust internal parameters for optimal operation"""
```

6.3 Communication Protocols

· Inter-Layer: QUENNE Internal Protocol (QIP) over RDMA
· External API: RESTful with GraphQL for complex queries
· Streaming: WebRTC with QUIC for real-time data
· Security: TLS 1.3 with post-quantum cryptography

