8. SAFETY AND COMPLIANCE

8.1 Fail-Safe Mechanisms

· Quantum Decay Detection: Automatic shutdown if coherence drops below threshold
· Neuromorphic Overload Protection: Rate limiting on spike frequency
· Edge Node Isolation: Physical disconnection capability
· Manual Override: Hardwired emergency stop on all critical components

8.2 Ethical Constraints

· Asimov-like Rules: Hardcoded in quantum state initialization
· Transparency Requirement: All decisions logged with reasoning
· Human-in-the-Loop: Critical decisions require human confirmation
· Bias Monitoring: Continuous audit for discriminatory patterns

8.3 Regulatory Compliance

· Data Protection: GDPR, CCPA, and emerging quantum privacy regulations
· Medical: FDA Class III if used in healthcare diagnostics
· Automotive: ISO 26262 ASIL-D if used in vehicles
· Aviation: DO-178C Level A if used in flight systems

