10. GLOSSARY OF TERMS

· Quantum State Inference: Reasoning using quantum probability amplitudes
· Associative Memory Field: Content-addressable memory with pattern completion
· 6G Semantic Signaling: Communication that includes meaning and intent
· Homeostatic Regulation: Self-maintenance of optimal operating conditions
· Edge-Actuated Intelligence: Decision-making and action at network periphery
· Cognitive Physics: Principles governing machine cognition as physical processes
· State-Aware Computation: Processing that considers the system's current cognitive state
· Neuromorphic Sensory Enaction: Perception-action loop using brain-inspired hardware

